  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Anastomotic leakage (AL) is one of the most-feared postoperative complications after anterior
      resection of rectal cancer. This complication compromises both short term and long term
      outcome of patients. The incidence of AL after anterior resection was approximately 6-11%.
      Although several risk factors for AL such as male sex, smoking, tumor location, longer
      operative time, intraoperative blood loss had been reported in previous studies, the
      incidence of AL did not meet a significant decrease. So far there is no multi-site
      observational study on incidence and risk factors of AL after anterior resection in China,
      therefore this study aims to work on this issue and provide evidence for clinical practice.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
